gw.api.builder

Class NonSubmissionJobBuilder<B extends NonSubmissionJobBuilder<B>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<PolicyPeriod,B>
      • gw.api.builder.JobBuilder<B>
        • gw.api.builder.NonSubmissionJobBuilder<B>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<PolicyPeriod>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CancellationBuilder, IssuanceBuilder, PolicyChangeBuilder, ReinstatementBuilder, RenewalBuilder, RewriteBuilder, RewriteNewAccountBuilder

    public abstract class NonSubmissionJobBuilder<B extends NonSubmissionJobBuilder<B>>
extends JobBuilder<B>

    Abstract superclass for builders which construct Jobs that normally have a BasedOn period. Provides support for these additional properties:

    • BasedOnPeriod
    • BranchNumber
    • PolicyNumber
    PolicyNumber can either be specified explicitly via withPolicyNumber(String), or set to an unassigned value using withUnassignedPolicyNumber(). If neither is specified, the PolicyNumber will be inherited normally from the BasedOn period.

    You can create a NonSubmissionJobBuilder and not specify a BasedOn period. It is up to the subclass to handle this, typically by calling maybeCreateBasedOnPeriod(Bundle) at the start of its DataBuilder.createBean(BuilderContext) method.

    • Constructor Detail

      • NonSubmissionJobBuilder

        protected NonSubmissionJobBuilder()
        Create a NonSubmissionJobBuilder. By default it is set up to inherit PolicyNumber, and specifies the product code to be used if the builder supplies the BasedOn period.

        The populator to handle PolicyNumber runs at POSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_0.
